</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="4" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,153,827]" pageId="4">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,315,765,791]" pageId="4">Remarks.</emphasis>
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jałoszyński" authorityYear="2019" box="[322,564,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Veraphis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aomoriensis">
<emphasis box="[322,564,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="4">Veraphis aomoriensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
belongs to the 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jaloszynski &amp; Hoshina" authorityYear="2005" box="[734,827,765,791]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Veraphis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="sawadai">
<emphasis box="[734,827,765,791]" italics="true" pageId="4">sawadai</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group of species, and is sympatric with 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Jałoszyński" authorityYear="2019" box="[1279,1429,766,791]" class="Insecta" family="Staphylinidae" genus="Veraphis" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF,CoL" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="4" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="mutsuensis">
<emphasis box="[1279,1429,766,791]" italics="true" pageId="4">V. mutsuensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. It is unique among members of this group in having the aedeagus with rounded instead of emarginate apex.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
